All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    DirectoryProcessor
    The driver of the file processor.
    ErrorsFactory
    The ErrorFactory has members as Strings, which hold for every possible error in the program.
    Filter
    This is an abstract class for the different filtering strategies.
    FilterAll
    This is the filter by default, and it doesn't filter any file.
    FilterBetween
    Filter all files with size between two numbers of KB.
    FilterContains
    Filter all files contains a given String in their absolute name.
    FilterExecutable
    Filter all executable files.
    FilterFile
    Filter all files have name that equals to a given String.
    FilterGreaterThan
    Filter all files with size bigger than a given number of KB.
    FilterHidden
    Filter all hidden files.
    FilterPrefix
    Filter all files starts with a given prefix.
    FiltersFactory
    The Filter Strategy Factory is a singleton with which produces a filters methods from a raw input.
    FilterSmallerThan
    Filter all files with size smaller than a given number of KB.
    FilterSuffix
    Filter all files end with a given suffix.
    FilterWritable
    Filter all writable files.
    ParametersFormat
    Interface to gather the format variables of the filter parameters line in the command file.
    ParametersFormat
    Interface to gather the format variables of the order parameters line in the command file.
    Section
    This is an object represents one section in the command file.
    SectionsFactory
    This sections factory parse the command file into different sections: Every section has a filtering method and an ordering method.
    SortAbsolute
    Sort files due to their absolute name, alphabetically.
    SortsFactory
    The Sort Strategy Factory is a singleton which produces sorting methods due a raw input line.
    SortSize
    Sort the files due their size from smallest to largest.
    SortStrategy
    Abstract class for the different Sorting strategies.
    SortType
    Sort files by their type.
    Type1Exception
    This is a class for Exceptions caused by bad parameters or parsing problem in the command file.
    Type2Exception
    This is a class for Exceptions caused by an essential error: 1) Invalid usage 2) I/O problem 3) Wrong Section's sub-sections names 4) Bad format of the command file
